# DPDP Act 2023 â€“ Healthcare Mapping

The DPDP Act, 2023 introduces a rights-based framework for
personal data protection in India, with significant implications
for healthcare institutions.

## Key Healthcare Data Types
- Patient demographic data
- Clinical records & reports
- Diagnostic images (PACS)
- Billing & insurance data
- Staff & clinician information

## Core DPDP Principles Applied to Healthcare
- Lawful purpose & consent
- Data minimization
- Purpose limitation
- Accuracy & integrity
- Storage limitation
- Security safeguards

## Practical Implementation
- Role-based access to patient data
- Logging and audit trails
- Consent capture & documentation
- Data retention and archival policies
- Vendor data processing agreements
